reviews.review_text:
Absolutely Marvelous--Start To Finish great show, great recording, great remastering.

the band gives their all.

the entire proceedings is captured with unyielding grace.

you must play this loudly to reach the full effect.

If you do, you will achieve nirvana.


that is the guarantee. The Evan S. Hunt guarantee.

vg show for most part Vg show overall. Though he's a wonderful player in general, Horsnby leaves me scratching my head some times. He absolutely butchers what could have been a beautiful BROKEDOWN PALACE, with his aggressive, loud and staccato accordian playing. Sometimes he just sticks out too much when he could do more service to the group by blending (or, in this case, not choosing a mid-heavy inappropriate instrument).

sweet Picasso Moon
Saint Of Circumstance ->

bruce brings a hugeness i enjoy

a millermasterpiece

My Holy Grail of Shows I finally found my Dark Star at this show, after about 60 or so stretching back to 1979. It was well worth the wait!

Overall, a spectacular, if not transcendent show. It felt very nice to be in the old Boston Garden.
Perfect capstone to a six night run that would become a tradition for the band in the fall.

Cheers!
